# Deployment Protocol

- **`dev`:** Staging / testing environment (`dev.buddget.online`).
- **`main`:** Production (`buddget.online` / primary Vercel production branch).

## Branch rules

- **Never create feature branches.** Always work directly on the `dev` branch.
- **Never push to `main` automatically.** Only merge and push to `main` when the user explicitly asks for it.

## Validation before any push

- When application code changed: run **`npm test`** (and fix failures) before pushing.
- Prefer a full local CI parity check when practical: `npm run lint`, `npm run test`, `npm run build`.

## Push workflow

1. Commit on `dev` and push: `git push -u origin dev`.
2. **Stop.** Do not touch `main` unless the user says so.
3. When the user explicitly requests a push to production: `git checkout main && git pull origin main && git merge dev && git push -u origin main`, then switch back to `dev`.

For small doc-only or rules-only changes, `npm test` may be optional if no runtime code changed; still run it when unsure.
